NAME
    mf2fasta - Converts a masterfile into fasta format

DESCRIPTION
    mf2fasta  takes only one argument, the name of the masterfile to be
    converted. By default, the converted masterfile is sent to standard out.A
    If no arguments are supplied, the usage is displayed.

OPTIONS
    mf2fasta [-n -c <num char/line> -o <outfile> -h] masterfile

    All options are optional.

     -n
        Print sequence position on each line
     -c integer
        Number of characters per line
     -o filename
        Send the output to file (default standard out)
     -h
        Display the usage

SEE ALSO
